Letter on behalf of the Defendant, received and filed.

Defendant Tonya L Garrett in court with attorney Daniel E Meylink.  Patricia I. Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 48 MONTHS, concurrent to COUNT 2 and consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 2 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 24 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 
AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 48 MONTHS, concurrent to COUNT 1 and consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 2 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 24 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 
Court STAYED the sentence in COUNT 1 and COUNT 2 and placed defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION as to COUNT 1 ONLY:
Court ordered defendant to serve 12 MONTHS condition time in the House of Correction; without good time credit, with release to the Day Reporting Center only and employment. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring.  
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION AND EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

- Maintain Absolute Sobriety, no alcohol.
- No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid 
  prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
  and successfully complete recommended treatment
  including drug and alcohol testing. 
- Obtain/Maintain Full Time employment/school or a combination of both. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- Defendant is not to possess cash currency in an amount greater than $200.00.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm holster, or any body armor.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
AS TO COUNT 1 and 2: Defendant to pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. 
Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately dueor civil judgment to be entered. 

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.
Court advises the Defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the Defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The Defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the Defendant being returned to prison.
